ub199.ezboard.com/bcolossusoflanys.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nizumyentalonheart>Nizumyen Talonheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(4/17/03 9:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub199.ezboard.com/fcolossusoflanysfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hate list / Tanks Taunting </span><hr size=1> I could load Terror of Darkness or one in that line of spells which adds hate...I used to call those spells save the caster when i used them in DL and other places a few lvls ago.  seemed to work well and since i've been playin SA then wouldn't be a bad idea.<br>
<br>
 just an idea<br>
                  Niz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub199.ezboard.com/bcolossusoflanys.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krby71>krby71</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#330000>(4/17/03 9:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub199.ezboard.com/fcolossusoflanysfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hate list / Tanks Taunting </span><hr size=1> Usually it is the job of the Secondary Assist (if assigned) or the Ranger (sometimes Rogue or Monk) to pull mobs off healers/casters.<br>
<br>
Rangers have many High Aggro low mana spells at their disposal (Debuffs like Immolate, Movement reduction like ensnare, plus DD, and DoT's) We tend to hit the mob very often, we have taunt and disarm.<br>
<br>
Rangers can grab aggro fairly quickly bring the mob to the MA/SA then dump aggro (jolt) or tank the mob for a while.<br>
<br>
Part of my (as well as most rangers) SOP when I am not MA is to watch my healers/casters to see if they have any unwanted aggro (which means any aggro)  If the MOB isn't the MA's mob and there isn't a SA I will get the mob off them.  If I die, no biggie.  If the Cleric dies, that is a bigger problem.<br>
<br>
I have created a &quot;Pulling &lt;MOB&gt; off &lt;Healer/Caster&gt;&quot; hotkey so the rest of the part knows what is going on.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.swbell.net/kb71/EQ/new5_ghaani_sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
